WHENEVER the weather reaches high temperatures, people jump into the pool to cool down. But for one man, this did not go according to plan. Partygoers were shocked when a man was discovered dead after disappearing into a sinkhole in a swimming pool. Over 50 people were attending a work pool party at a villa in the Israeli town of Karmei Yosef. The Mirror reports that the 30-year-old man was sucked underground when the bottom of the pool collapsed. READ: PICS: RESIDENTS BIG SINKHOLE NIGHTMARE Terrifying footage shows swimmers hanging on to the edges of the pool as the water drains rapidly and inflatables disappeared underground. According to the publication, after a four-hour rescue operation, the man’s body was located at the end of a 15m tunnel. Rescue crews used Go-Pro cameras to look for the man in a large pit under the pool. One partygoer said: “The water level suddenly started receding and a hole opened up, creating a tidal wave that swept two people inside.”